WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:10.844 --> 00:00:15.056 position:50% align:center
[CONVENTION GUESTS chatter]

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:18.685 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST A]
One copy, please!

00:00:18.768 --> 00:00:20.645 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE WORKER A]
That'll be 500 yen!

00:00:20.729 --> 00:00:21.855 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE GUEST A]
Hi, can I get two?

00:00:21.938 --> 00:00:23.898 position:50% align:center
[MALE WORKER A]
You bet! 1,000 yen.

00:00:29.654 --> 00:00:33.950 position:50% align:center
No contest, I guess.
Looks like I'm gonna win, sorry.

00:00:34.034 --> 00:00:36.286 position:50% align:center
Just keep telling
yourself that.

00:00:36.369 --> 00:00:38.413 position:50% align:center
Right, girls. You ready?

00:00:38.496 --> 00:00:40.040 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Yeah!

00:00:43.293 --> 00:00:44.627 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:46.796 position:50% align:center
While you guys were
busy making the manga,

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.966 position:50% align:center
we were putting these
saucy outfits together!

00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:51.259 position:50% align:center
Don't underestimate us,

00:00:51.343 --> 00:00:54.471 position:50% align:center
'cause we'll do whatever
it takes to win!

00:00:54.554 --> 00:00:59.559 position:50% align:center
♪

00:02:24.644 --> 00:02:27.147 position:50% align:center
Comes see us at the
"Ratatoskr" booth!

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:31.109 position:50% align:center
Our manga's gonna sell fast,
so you better come and get it!

00:02:31.192 --> 00:02:33.236 position:50% align:center
Whoa, my dudes, check out
all the smokin' hot babes

00:02:33.319 --> 00:02:34.571 position:50% align:center
at that booth over there.

00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:36.948 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST C] I didn't see
them in the catalogue!

00:02:37.032 --> 00:02:39.659 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST D gasps]
Well, what have we got here?

00:02:39.743 --> 00:02:41.327 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA]
Oh! Thanks for your business!

00:02:41.411 --> 00:02:42.912 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST D]
Huh? Uh, I was just--

00:02:42.996 --> 00:02:45.331 position:50% align:center
That's 500 yen, please! In cash!

00:02:45.415 --> 00:02:48.084 position:50% align:center
Okay... One copy.

00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.961 position:50% align:center
Wow! My first sale, thanks!

00:02:50.045 --> 00:02:51.338 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST D]
Uh, sure. Ow.

00:02:51.421 --> 00:02:54.591 position:50% align:center
[chuckles] I guess that's
one sales strategy.

00:02:54.674 --> 00:02:57.344 position:50% align:center
[CONVENTION GUESTS chatter]

00:02:57.427 --> 00:02:59.971 position:50% align:center
Line up! The Ratatoskr
queue starts here, folks!

00:03:00.055 --> 00:03:02.766 position:50% align:center
That's right, friends!
Kindly form two lines, please!

00:03:02.849 --> 00:03:05.727 position:50% align:center
It got busy fast around here,
must be the bunnies.

00:03:05.810 --> 00:03:07.103 position:50% align:center
[REINE]
Two, please.

00:03:07.187 --> 00:03:08.563 position:50% align:center
Oh, uh, sure!

00:03:08.646 --> 00:03:10.273 position:50% align:center
Wait, huh?!

00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:16.196 position:50% align:center
Yup. We asked the Ratatoskr
crew to help out.

00:03:16.279 --> 00:03:18.990 position:50% align:center
We've resorted to
using shills, have we?

00:03:19.074 --> 00:03:20.784 position:50% align:center
Hey, Tohka! We made it!

00:03:20.867 --> 00:03:21.659 position:50% align:center
How goes it?

00:03:21.743 --> 00:03:23.370 position:50% align:center
This place sure is packed, huh?

00:03:23.453 --> 00:03:24.871 position:50% align:center
That is so lame.

00:03:24.954 --> 00:03:27.499 position:50% align:center
Aw, I really appreciate
you guys showing up!

00:03:27.582 --> 00:03:29.084 position:50% align:center
Anything for you!

00:03:29.167 --> 00:03:31.503 position:50% align:center
Plus, it sounded like fun, so I
figured why not check it out?

00:03:31.586 --> 00:03:34.798 position:50% align:center
Yeah, same, and I've always
wanted to come to Comico.

00:03:34.881 --> 00:03:37.676 position:50% align:center
[AI]
Uh! Wow, even Itsuka's here!

00:03:37.759 --> 00:03:39.135 position:50% align:center
You helping Tohka?

00:03:39.219 --> 00:03:40.637 position:50% align:center
I am.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:44.140 position:50% align:center
[MAI]
Hm... Hey, call me crazy, but...

00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:47.310 position:50% align:center
...your manga's protagonist
looks an awful lot like Itsuka.

00:03:47.394 --> 00:03:48.978 position:50% align:center
[MII]
That is so lame.

00:03:49.062 --> 00:03:50.897 position:50% align:center
No! This is purely
a work of fiction!

00:03:50.980 --> 00:03:54.567 position:50% align:center
Any similarity to real people or
events is entirely coincidental!

00:03:54.651 --> 00:03:55.735 position:50% align:center
You're imagining it!

00:03:55.819 --> 00:03:57.946 position:50% align:center
Yeah, sure we are.

00:03:58.029 --> 00:04:00.740 position:50% align:center
I mean, spirits and a
secret organization?

00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:02.325 position:50% align:center
That is so lame.

00:04:02.409 --> 00:04:05.078 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps, chuckles]

00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:10.500 position:50% align:center
--[RYOKO] Origami.
--[ORIGAMI] Mm?

00:04:10.583 --> 00:04:13.545 position:50% align:center
It's rare for you to ask a
favor, so what is this about?

00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:18.008 position:50% align:center
Captain, Mikie, Mildred.
Thanks for coming.

00:04:18.091 --> 00:04:19.551 position:50% align:center
Hang on.

00:04:19.634 --> 00:04:21.845 position:50% align:center
Why do I feel like I've seen
those girls somewhere before.

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:25.598 position:50% align:center
You haven't.

00:04:25.682 --> 00:04:28.143 position:50% align:center
You've been acting different
lately, Origami, what's up?

00:04:28.226 --> 00:04:29.394 position:50% align:center
Different?

00:04:29.477 --> 00:04:31.688 position:50% align:center
Wait, I'm confused.

00:04:31.771 --> 00:04:35.608 position:50% align:center
Do those people not remember the
world before I changed history?

00:04:36.735 --> 00:04:39.237 position:50% align:center
No, but we Spirits remember,

00:04:39.320 --> 00:04:41.865 position:50% align:center
'cause we're connected to
you through Spirit power.

00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:44.909 position:50% align:center
Those people don't
have that connection.

00:04:44.993 --> 00:04:48.538 position:50% align:center
[GUESTS, WORKERS chattering]

00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:50.248 position:50% align:center
We've got five boxes left.

00:04:50.331 --> 00:04:52.417 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:04:52.500 --> 00:04:55.128 position:50% align:center
I guess it's no use.
We'll never beat her.

00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:57.255 position:50% align:center
[NIA] Of course not.
Know what people want?

00:04:57.339 --> 00:04:58.381 position:50% align:center
A good read.

00:04:58.465 --> 00:05:01.301 position:50% align:center
Not some convoluted,
amateurish drivel.

00:05:01.384 --> 00:05:04.637 position:50% align:center
You had already lost the
game before it even started.

00:05:04.721 --> 00:05:07.640 position:50% align:center
Cheap bunny-suits can't hold a
candle to a good story.

00:05:07.724 --> 00:05:09.559 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:05:09.642 --> 00:05:12.687 position:50% align:center
This isn't over yet!
We're just getting started here!

00:05:12.771 --> 00:05:13.980 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Huh?

00:05:18.526 --> 00:05:20.737 position:50% align:center
All right, friends,
it's showtime!

00:05:22.405 --> 00:05:29.162 position:50% align:center
[GUESTS shouting, screaming]

00:05:29.245 --> 00:05:30.997 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST E]
It's actually her!

00:05:31.081 --> 00:05:34.250 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST F] No way! What is
a star like her doing here?

00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:35.877 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST G] Can we really,
like shake your hand?

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:39.130 position:50% align:center
You can! And your support
means so much to me.

00:05:39.214 --> 00:05:40.465 position:50% align:center
I'm getting emotional!

00:05:40.548 --> 00:05:42.592 position:50% align:center
[GUESTS cheer]

00:05:42.676 --> 00:05:44.135 position:50% align:center
Are you sure you wanna do this?

00:05:44.219 --> 00:05:46.930 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we all know how
much you hate men.

00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:49.140 position:50% align:center
My Darling has given
it his best, and so has

00:05:49.224 --> 00:05:53.186 position:50% align:center
everyone else, so I refuse to
stand idly by doing nothing!

00:05:53.269 --> 00:05:55.689 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna step up,
even if it's uncomfortable!

00:05:55.772 --> 00:05:57.857 position:50% align:center
Sometimes you just have
to take one for the team!

00:05:57.941 --> 00:05:58.900 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUEST H]
You're really pretty!

00:05:58.983 --> 00:06:01.236 position:50% align:center
Thanks, that's sweet
of you to say!

00:06:01.319 --> 00:06:03.571 position:50% align:center
Huh. Well, I'm impressed.

00:06:03.655 --> 00:06:05.615 position:50% align:center
That girl's
legitimately famous, huh?

00:06:05.699 --> 00:06:07.534 position:50% align:center
That's right. She's an idol.

00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:10.161 position:50% align:center
We're very proud of her.

00:06:10.245 --> 00:06:13.123 position:50% align:center
[NIA] Hm. Still, do you really
think you'll catch up to me?

00:06:13.206 --> 00:06:15.208 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Catch and surpass.

00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:17.460 position:50% align:center
For our sake, sure.
But yours, too.

00:06:17.544 --> 00:06:19.129 position:50% align:center
Just wait and see.

00:06:19.212 --> 00:06:23.717 position:50% align:center
[NIA laughing]
Listen to you!

00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:27.012 position:50% align:center
Maybe you're right, but we
won't know till you win.

00:06:27.095 --> 00:06:28.013 position:50% align:center
[HIROKI]
Miss Honjo?

00:06:28.096 --> 00:06:29.556 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO, NIA]
Huh?

00:06:32.225 --> 00:06:33.852 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Hm...

00:06:33.935 --> 00:06:35.895 position:50% align:center
Y-Yes, um...

00:06:37.480 --> 00:06:41.151 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Oh, Takajo. It's you.

00:06:41.234 --> 00:06:42.569 position:50% align:center
[HIROKI chuckles nervously]

00:06:42.652 --> 00:06:44.237 position:50% align:center
I know, it's been a while,
but when I heard you were

00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:45.739 position:50% align:center
participating in Comico,

00:06:45.822 --> 00:06:47.824 position:50% align:center
I figured I had to stop
by and say hello.

00:06:47.907 --> 00:06:49.242 position:50% align:center
I just couldn't not, you know?

00:06:49.325 --> 00:06:52.162 position:50% align:center
Uh, right.

00:06:52.245 --> 00:06:55.248 position:50% align:center
Um, Kotori, did you know
she was going to show up?

00:06:55.331 --> 00:06:56.791 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Mm-mm.

00:06:56.875 --> 00:07:00.253 position:50% align:center
Sorry to show up like this, but
something's been bothering me.

00:07:00.337 --> 00:07:01.838 position:50% align:center
I have to ask you about it.

00:07:01.921 --> 00:07:05.800 position:50% align:center
Have I said or done something
unknowingly to upset you.

00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:07.385 position:50% align:center
Are you mad at me
for some reason?

00:07:07.469 --> 00:07:09.471 position:50% align:center
If so, I want to apologize.

00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:11.765 position:50% align:center
That's not it
at all, I just...

00:07:11.848 --> 00:07:15.143 position:50% align:center
[gasps] But I also want
you to know that,

00:07:15.226 --> 00:07:18.688 position:50% align:center
even if you do hate me,
I'll always read your work.

00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:21.191 position:50% align:center
I want to support you
'cause you're great.

00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:23.693 position:50% align:center
[NIA gasps]

00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.195 position:50% align:center
[HIROKI]
Mm.

00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:28.782 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Hm.

00:07:28.865 --> 00:07:32.035 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
I finally get it.

00:07:32.118 --> 00:07:34.454 position:50% align:center
It's because you really
care about her, don't you?

00:07:34.537 --> 00:07:37.082 position:50% align:center
What nonsense are you
blathering on about, Boy?

00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:39.542 position:50% align:center
Don't play dumb. You didn't
distance yourself from her

00:07:39.626 --> 00:07:41.711 position:50% align:center
'cause you discovered
she had a dark side.

00:07:41.795 --> 00:07:43.505 position:50% align:center
You just don't trust yourself.

00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:45.632 position:50% align:center
You're scared you'll get
curious and take a peek

00:07:45.715 --> 00:07:47.050 position:50% align:center
in that book of yours.

00:07:47.133 --> 00:07:50.095 position:50% align:center
And you'll find out things
about her you don't like.

00:07:50.178 --> 00:07:51.554 position:50% align:center
[NIA sighs]

00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:54.140 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] So, afraid of being
let down, you pulled away.

00:07:54.224 --> 00:07:55.475 position:50% align:center
Am I right?

00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:57.060 position:50% align:center
Ha! Shows what you know.

00:07:57.143 --> 00:07:59.479 position:50% align:center
It's a good thing you're
not a therapist, Boy!

00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:01.690 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Hi! Five hundred yen, please!

00:08:01.773 --> 00:08:03.525 position:50% align:center
Well, tell me what it is, then!

00:08:03.608 --> 00:08:05.318 position:50% align:center
Do you just hate
people for no reason,

00:08:05.402 --> 00:08:07.237 position:50% align:center
even when you get
along with them?

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:10.490 position:50% align:center
Would you shut up already?
Focus on your booth, okay?

00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:11.866 position:50% align:center
Sorry, you wanted two, right?

00:08:11.950 --> 00:08:13.326 position:50% align:center
I am not letting this go!

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:15.578 position:50% align:center
Come on, Shido,
we need you, stat!

00:08:15.662 --> 00:08:17.580 position:50% align:center
I'm trying to win
'cause I wanna help!

00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.165 position:50% align:center
Stop running from things!

00:08:19.249 --> 00:08:21.751 position:50% align:center
That won't make your problems
go away, and you know it!

00:08:21.835 --> 00:08:23.253 position:50% align:center
Thank you, here's your change!

00:08:23.336 --> 00:08:25.380 position:50% align:center
[NIA grunts]
So what if I'm afraid?

00:08:25.463 --> 00:08:26.840 position:50% align:center
I've got legit reasons!

00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:29.217 position:50% align:center
I can "take a peek" into
people's private lives anytime

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.761 position:50% align:center
I want! How am I supposed
to forge real friendships?

00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:34.139 position:50% align:center
Until you take that risk,
you'll never know the answer!

00:08:34.222 --> 00:08:35.432 position:50% align:center
Would you do it?

00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:36.891 position:50% align:center
Open your heart to
someone who could peer

00:08:36.975 --> 00:08:38.852 position:50% align:center
into your private life
whenever they want?

00:08:38.935 --> 00:08:41.980 position:50% align:center
Can learn your darkest secrets
and use them against you?

00:08:42.063 --> 00:08:44.315 position:50% align:center
I can flip open Rasiel and
spy on you in the bathtub

00:08:44.399 --> 00:08:46.484 position:50% align:center
or on the toilet,
does that sound like fun?

00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:50.530 position:50% align:center
Being my friend means worrying
every time you use the bathroom!

00:08:50.613 --> 00:08:52.198 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO laughs]

00:08:52.282 --> 00:08:54.325 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
What? What's so funny?

00:08:54.409 --> 00:08:55.744 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Sorry, but that's hilarious,

00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:57.037 position:50% align:center
and it doesn't faze me.

00:08:57.120 --> 00:08:58.038 position:50% align:center
Not in the least.

00:08:58.121 --> 00:08:59.998 position:50% align:center
Privacy? What's that?

00:09:00.081 --> 00:09:01.791 position:50% align:center
In fact, I think you're
a saint for caring

00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.126 position:50% align:center
how you affect people!

00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:04.210 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:09:04.294 --> 00:09:06.338 position:50% align:center
If you wanna peep on me,
go right ahead!

00:09:06.421 --> 00:09:09.507 position:50% align:center
I don't care, and I'm never
gonna hate you for it!

00:09:09.591 --> 00:09:10.884 position:50% align:center
[NIA gasps]

00:09:10.967 --> 00:09:12.594 position:50% align:center
[MALE WORKER A] Sensei!
We're down to just one copy!

00:09:12.677 --> 00:09:14.846 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA]
Shido, this is our last one!

00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:16.306 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO, NIA]
Thank you for your business!

00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:17.974 position:50% align:center
[NATSUMI]
Ratatoskr: sold out!

00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:19.809 position:50% align:center
[MALE WORKER A]
Honjo: sold out!

00:09:23.021 --> 00:09:26.483 position:50% align:center
Well, well. It looks like
we ended up in a tie.

00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:28.651 position:50% align:center
[NIA chuckles]
Fine.

00:09:28.735 --> 00:09:31.446 position:50% align:center
Since you guys put up such a
good fight, I'll say, "Uncle".

00:09:31.529 --> 00:09:32.572 position:50% align:center
Guess I'll read it.

00:09:32.655 --> 00:09:36.659 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp, giggle]

00:09:38.036 --> 00:09:40.663 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Ugh, seriously?

00:09:40.747 --> 00:09:44.250 position:50% align:center
Hmm. That's interesting.

00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:46.920 position:50% align:center
A sweet little tale about
Shido Itsuka saving Spirits,

00:09:47.003 --> 00:09:48.838 position:50% align:center
how very meta indeed.

00:09:48.922 --> 00:09:51.257 position:50% align:center
It's better than I thought
it would be, but still.

00:09:51.341 --> 00:09:52.967 position:50% align:center
I have some thoughts.

00:09:53.051 --> 00:09:55.595 position:50% align:center
It just packs too much
into one volume.

00:09:55.679 --> 00:09:56.888 position:50% align:center
With eight Spirits,

00:09:56.971 --> 00:09:58.682 position:50% align:center
there aren't enough pages
to flesh things out.

00:09:58.765 --> 00:10:01.976 position:50% align:center
Not enough time to fall
for the main character.

00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:03.520 position:50% align:center
Though I have to say,

00:10:03.603 --> 00:10:06.064 position:50% align:center
it's not bad considering the
time crunch they were all under.

00:10:06.147 --> 00:10:07.941 position:50% align:center
How did they make it in time?

00:10:08.024 --> 00:10:09.234 position:50% align:center
Let's find out.

00:10:11.986 --> 00:10:15.240 position:50% align:center
[NATSUMI] And I plan on showing
that silly-head, Nia, too.

00:10:15.323 --> 00:10:18.451 position:50% align:center
Having friends is
the best thing ever.

00:10:23.748 --> 00:10:25.750 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:30.547 position:50% align:center
[NIA] Everything they wrote,
it was all true?

00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:33.383 position:50% align:center
Even the nice things
that Shido said?

00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:43.810 position:50% align:center
Nia.

00:10:46.187 --> 00:10:49.149 position:50% align:center
What'd you think?
Did we do okay?

00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:51.860 position:50% align:center
I mean, it's all right--
I will give you that.

00:10:51.943 --> 00:10:54.612 position:50% align:center
But it's a bit naïve to think
a manga alone would do it.

00:10:54.696 --> 00:10:56.656 position:50% align:center
That it'd be enough to
make me fall for you.

00:10:56.740 --> 00:10:58.408 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:03.997 position:50% align:center
But, that said, I found the
whole thing pretty moving.

00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:06.916 position:50% align:center
I guess what I'm saying is, I'm
open to giving you another shot.

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.002 position:50% align:center
--[SHIDO gasps]
--[NIA] Oh, for the love of--!

00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:11.838 position:50% align:center
Are you dense? I'm going
on another date with you!

00:11:11.921 --> 00:11:15.425 position:50% align:center
So, if you know what's good for
you, you'd better make it count!

00:11:15.508 --> 00:11:17.427 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:11:17.510 --> 00:11:21.598 position:50% align:center
[ALL cheer]

00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:24.142 position:50% align:center
[MIKU]
You did it, Darling!

00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:28.438 position:50% align:center
[NIA] Mm. I think it's a bit
early to start celebrating,

00:11:28.521 --> 00:11:29.939 position:50% align:center
but I'm looking forward to--

00:11:30.023 --> 00:11:31.524 position:50% align:center
[NIA gasps]

00:11:33.610 --> 00:11:38.823 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:11:38.907 --> 00:11:40.241 position:50% align:center
Nia, what's wrong?

00:11:40.325 --> 00:11:42.827 position:50% align:center
[alarm]

00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:44.829 position:50% align:center
What? The spatial
quake alarm?

00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:46.331 position:50% align:center
Nia! Can we help?

00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:49.167 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Reine, what's happening?

00:11:49.250 --> 00:11:52.962 position:50% align:center
Spirit Level: Category E!
It appears Nia is inverting!

00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:54.339 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:55.423 --> 00:12:00.428 position:50% align:center
[screams]

00:12:25.328 --> 00:12:29.082 position:50% align:center
[alarm]

00:12:29.165 --> 00:12:30.750 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER A]
Spatial quake warning.

00:12:30.834 --> 00:12:33.670 position:50% align:center
Please evacuate to the
nearest shelter immediately.

00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.464 position:50% align:center
[WESTCOTT]
Well, look at that.

00:12:36.548 --> 00:12:38.967 position:50% align:center
Sister inverted,
just as planned.

00:12:39.050 --> 00:12:41.678 position:50% align:center
But why would it
happen now, Ike?

00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:43.304 position:50% align:center
We put her through agony.

00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:45.515 position:50% align:center
It was five straight
years of torture.

00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:48.852 position:50% align:center
She withstood unthinkable
physical and mental strife.

00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:50.729 position:50% align:center
And yet, no matter
what we did to her,

00:12:50.812 --> 00:12:52.647 position:50% align:center
not once could we
make her invert.

00:12:52.731 --> 00:12:55.817 position:50% align:center
Before us, Sister had already
lost her faith in humanity

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:58.153 position:50% align:center
and become jaded
with the world.

00:12:58.236 --> 00:12:59.320 position:50% align:center
That's why I did it.

00:12:59.404 --> 00:13:01.781 position:50% align:center
Why I allowed her to escape.

00:13:01.865 --> 00:13:05.118 position:50% align:center
[ELLEN gasps] So, what was the
purpose of the micro-Realizer

00:13:05.201 --> 00:13:06.619 position:50% align:center
you planted in her brain?

00:13:06.703 --> 00:13:09.122 position:50% align:center
I wanted to make doubly sure
she forgot all the pain

00:13:09.205 --> 00:13:11.624 position:50% align:center
and suffering we
put her through.

00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:14.794 position:50% align:center
But then, the instant she
opened her heart to Shido,

00:13:14.878 --> 00:13:17.589 position:50% align:center
and began to regain
her trust in humanity,

00:13:17.672 --> 00:13:21.134 position:50% align:center
she remembered those five
terrible years of anguish.

00:13:22.385 --> 00:13:25.221 position:50% align:center
[WESTCOTT] It's just like glass.
The higher the height

00:13:25.305 --> 00:13:28.892 position:50% align:center
from which it falls, the more
completely it shatters.

00:13:28.975 --> 00:13:30.977 position:50% align:center
I'll be counting
on you, too.

00:13:31.061 --> 00:13:34.147 position:50% align:center
Ellen and I both rely
on your assistance.

00:13:37.567 --> 00:13:39.611 position:50% align:center
Beelzebub.

00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:43.365 position:50% align:center
Is that--?

00:13:43.448 --> 00:13:45.533 position:50% align:center
Be careful, Shido!

00:13:45.617 --> 00:13:47.410 position:50% align:center
It's from her Demon King.

00:14:02.717 --> 00:14:04.052 position:50% align:center
Metatron!

00:14:07.806 --> 00:14:09.015 position:50% align:center
Whatever is going on here,

00:14:09.099 --> 00:14:11.226 position:50% align:center
we simply cannot
allow it to continue.

00:14:11.309 --> 00:14:12.560 position:50% align:center
I agree--we can't,

00:14:12.644 --> 00:14:14.562 position:50% align:center
but you should let us
take care of things here.

00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:16.064 position:50% align:center
You go help Nia, and--

00:14:16.147 --> 00:14:19.401 position:50% align:center
Sorry, but I'm not
gonna let that happen.

00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:23.780 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Ellen!

00:14:23.863 --> 00:14:25.907 position:50% align:center
Oh, of course, given your
impeccable timing,

00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:29.119 position:50% align:center
I think it's safe to assume you
guys are responsible for this.

00:14:29.202 --> 00:14:32.080 position:50% align:center
Your Demon King's power presents
a troublesome challenge.

00:14:32.163 --> 00:14:35.291 position:50% align:center
Let's finish this little saga
as fast as we can.

00:14:36.543 --> 00:14:37.293 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:14:37.377 --> 00:14:38.795 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA]
Sandalphon!

00:14:41.172 --> 00:14:43.591 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Kaguya, Yuzuru, Miku!
Take Ellen!

00:14:43.675 --> 00:14:46.511 position:50% align:center
Origami, Yoshino, and Natsumi,
you help Shido!

00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:47.804 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Right!

00:14:49.723 --> 00:14:51.182 position:50% align:center
Nia!

00:14:52.851 --> 00:14:55.145 position:50% align:center
What's happening?
Why can't I move?

00:14:56.855 --> 00:14:58.440 position:50% align:center
Future Entry!

00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:01.484 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI, SHIDO gasp]

00:15:01.568 --> 00:15:03.778 position:50% align:center
Leave this part to me!
Let's go, Zadkiel!

00:15:03.862 --> 00:15:06.865 position:50% align:center
[YOSHINON] Move it!
You guys are in our way!

00:15:11.494 --> 00:15:12.787 position:50% align:center
Haniel!

00:15:19.044 --> 00:15:20.337 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:24.341 position:50% align:center
[roars]

00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:27.093 position:50% align:center
[YOSHINO]
What... is this?

00:15:27.177 --> 00:15:31.348 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Gah...! Ah!

00:15:31.431 --> 00:15:33.600 position:50% align:center
[NATSUMI]
What's going on?

00:15:33.683 --> 00:15:35.894 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] Wait, Is this
Future Entry again?

00:15:40.190 --> 00:15:41.191 position:50% align:center
Go, Shido.

00:15:41.274 --> 00:15:44.110 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO grunts]

00:15:44.194 --> 00:15:46.613 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:15:46.696 --> 00:15:48.239 position:50% align:center
Zadkiel!

00:15:50.784 --> 00:15:52.327 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Shido used Zadkiel!

00:15:52.410 --> 00:15:53.578 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO grunts]

00:15:53.661 --> 00:15:56.581 position:50% align:center
I can move? Oh, now I get it!

00:15:56.664 --> 00:15:59.584 position:50% align:center
It's because that
wasn't written down?

00:15:59.668 --> 00:16:02.462 position:50% align:center
And now I can fight! Sandalphon!

00:16:06.800 --> 00:16:08.593 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:16:08.677 --> 00:16:09.678 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Nia!

00:16:09.761 --> 00:16:12.889 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Wait. If I use Gabriel, then...!

00:16:14.933 --> 00:16:16.851 position:50% align:center
Nia!

00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:21.147 position:50% align:center
[NIA gasps]
Shi...do.

00:16:21.231 --> 00:16:23.900 position:50% align:center
Hang on! I will save you,
I promise!

00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.319 position:50% align:center
No, you won't.
Not if I can help it.

00:16:26.528 --> 00:16:29.030 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO shouts, grunts]

00:16:30.073 --> 00:16:31.282 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:34.369 --> 00:16:35.912 position:50% align:center
Nia!

00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:39.666 position:50% align:center
What are you even doing here,
Artemisia Ashcroft?

00:16:39.749 --> 00:16:41.459 position:50% align:center
Artemisia?

00:16:49.843 --> 00:16:52.804 position:50% align:center
[gasps, sighs]

00:16:54.014 --> 00:16:55.223 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:16:57.892 --> 00:16:59.602 position:50% align:center
That's Isaac Westcott!

00:16:59.686 --> 00:17:02.397 position:50% align:center
Well, long time no see,
Shido Itsuka.

00:17:02.480 --> 00:17:05.608 position:50% align:center
I'm delighted to see
you're looking well.

00:17:05.692 --> 00:17:08.111 position:50% align:center
Ah, but it's marvelous?

00:17:08.194 --> 00:17:11.906 position:50% align:center
Behold, the vision: a crystal
of inverted Spirit power.

00:17:11.990 --> 00:17:13.408 position:50% align:center
Qlipha!

00:17:15.869 --> 00:17:18.872 position:50% align:center
And now, at long last,
I take one great stride

00:17:18.955 --> 00:17:22.542 position:50% align:center
towards the fulfilment
of my deepest desires!

00:17:22.625 --> 00:17:27.630 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:35.180 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:35.263 --> 00:17:38.725 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:17:38.808 --> 00:17:42.062 position:50% align:center
No way! Did he just
absorb a Sephirah?

00:17:42.145 --> 00:17:45.065 position:50% align:center
Your eyes do not
betray you, Shido Itsuka.

00:17:45.148 --> 00:17:46.649 position:50% align:center
Observe.

00:17:46.733 --> 00:17:50.653 position:50% align:center
Just as you gained the powers of
the eight Spirits, I did this.

00:17:50.737 --> 00:17:52.238 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:52.322 --> 00:17:53.990 position:50% align:center
Beelzebub.

00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:03.208 position:50% align:center
Aha, curious, isn't it?

00:18:03.291 --> 00:18:06.086 position:50% align:center
Just by making physical
contact with a Demon King,

00:18:06.169 --> 00:18:09.547 position:50% align:center
one may learn exactly
how to use its power.

00:18:09.631 --> 00:18:10.965 position:50% align:center
[ELLEN gasps]
Ike!

00:18:12.175 --> 00:18:13.885 position:50% align:center
Do you see this, Ellen?

00:18:13.968 --> 00:18:16.137 position:50% align:center
Behold one of the
majestic Demon Kings

00:18:16.221 --> 00:18:18.807 position:50% align:center
which shall light
our path forward!

00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:22.268 position:50% align:center
Unfortunately, just one
Demon King will not suffice.

00:18:22.352 --> 00:18:25.647 position:50% align:center
It is not nearly enough to
satisfy our ambitions.

00:18:30.568 --> 00:18:32.070 position:50% align:center
[TOHKA shouts]

00:18:33.238 --> 00:18:34.447 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA grunts]

00:18:35.615 --> 00:18:37.117 position:50% align:center
Shido! Are you okay?

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:39.619 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I'm fine!
But I'm not sure about Nia!

00:18:41.162 --> 00:18:44.833 position:50% align:center
[WESTCOTT] Ellen, now that
we've achieved our goal,

00:18:44.916 --> 00:18:46.668 position:50% align:center
I think we should call it a day.

00:18:46.751 --> 00:18:48.044 position:50% align:center
[ELLEN]
What? Are you sure?

00:18:48.128 --> 00:18:50.588 position:50% align:center
Absorbing multiple Demon
Kings at once isn't easy,

00:18:50.672 --> 00:18:52.590 position:50% align:center
and even a body of
my caliber will struggle

00:18:52.674 --> 00:18:55.051 position:50% align:center
with completing that process.

00:18:55.135 --> 00:18:57.762 position:50% align:center
Besides, it would be a
criminal waste not to allow

00:18:57.846 --> 00:19:00.765 position:50% align:center
myself to savor each
and every one of them.

00:19:00.849 --> 00:19:02.892 position:50% align:center
[WESTCOTT] Tsk. We will
meet again soon,

00:19:02.976 --> 00:19:05.520 position:50% align:center
Shido Itsuka and Spirits.

00:19:05.603 --> 00:19:09.566 position:50% align:center
Someday, I'll make you invert,
just like I did poor Nia here.

00:19:09.649 --> 00:19:12.402 position:50% align:center
And then I will take
your Qlipha, as well.

00:19:12.485 --> 00:19:13.778 position:50% align:center
But in the meantime,

00:19:13.862 --> 00:19:16.656 position:50% align:center
I do hope you will enjoy
your final days of peace.

00:19:18.658 --> 00:19:21.119 position:50% align:center
--[KOTORI gasps]
--[SHIDO] Nia!

00:19:21.202 --> 00:19:24.539 position:50% align:center
Nia! Hey! Hang in there!

00:19:24.622 --> 00:19:26.082 position:50% align:center
[NIA grunts]

00:19:26.166 --> 00:19:29.794 position:50% align:center
Shido, wait! It's faint, but I
can sense her Spirit power!

00:19:29.878 --> 00:19:31.087 position:50% align:center
What, really?

00:19:31.171 --> 00:19:33.006 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] Just before
Artemisia stabbed Nia,

00:19:33.089 --> 00:19:34.924 position:50% align:center
you pulled part of Nia's
consciousness back,

00:19:35.008 --> 00:19:36.676 position:50% align:center
you must have saved it.

00:19:36.760 --> 00:19:41.765 position:50% align:center
So, at that point, Nia wasn't
fully inverted anymore.

00:19:41.848 --> 00:19:45.977 position:50% align:center
She probably has a fragment
of Sephirah left in her body.

00:19:46.061 --> 00:19:48.313 position:50% align:center
In other words,
you can seal her.

00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:55.612 position:50% align:center
Nia, please, open your
heart to me!

00:19:55.695 --> 00:20:00.533 position:50% align:center
I don't care if you use every
bit of my power. Please!

00:20:02.786 --> 00:20:03.953 position:50% align:center
[NIA gasps]

00:20:04.037 --> 00:20:06.373 position:50% align:center
Wake up, Nia! We're with you!

00:20:13.421 --> 00:20:14.464 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Nia!

00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:15.757 position:50% align:center
Yes!

00:20:17.592 --> 00:20:19.719 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:20:19.803 --> 00:20:22.389 position:50% align:center
Jeez, why are you
guys being so loud?

00:20:22.472 --> 00:20:24.474 position:50% align:center
I'm, like, two feet away,
you know.

00:20:24.557 --> 00:20:25.892 position:50% align:center
Sorry!

00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:29.938 position:50% align:center
Thank you, so much.

00:20:33.566 --> 00:20:38.571 position:50% align:center line:10%
♪

00:22:07.118 --> 00:22:08.161 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS gasp]

00:22:08.244 --> 00:22:10.372 position:50% align:center
[MIKU]
First sunrise of the year.

00:22:12.665 --> 00:22:15.919 position:50% align:center
Hey, Boy? I hope you know
how much this means.

00:22:16.002 --> 00:22:16.836 position:50% align:center
For real.

00:22:16.920 --> 00:22:18.129 position:50% align:center
Don't mention it.

00:22:18.213 --> 00:22:21.299 position:50% align:center
Besides, it's not
like I did it alone.

00:22:21.383 --> 00:22:25.887 position:50% align:center
And I did some serious thinking
while I was recovering.

00:22:25.970 --> 00:22:28.765 position:50% align:center
I decided I wanna patch
things up with Takajo,

00:22:28.848 --> 00:22:29.974 position:50% align:center
be friends again.

00:22:30.058 --> 00:22:31.810 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Yeah, that's a good call.

00:22:31.893 --> 00:22:33.978 position:50% align:center
Takajo's probably a good person.

00:22:34.062 --> 00:22:36.356 position:50% align:center
"Probably"?

00:22:36.439 --> 00:22:37.691 position:50% align:center
It's kinda weird.

00:22:37.774 --> 00:22:40.360 position:50% align:center
Yeah, it stinks to
have lost my power,

00:22:40.443 --> 00:22:42.862 position:50% align:center
but I also feel
at peace with it.

00:22:42.946 --> 00:22:45.490 position:50% align:center
I had Raziel for
almost 30 years,

00:22:45.573 --> 00:22:48.868 position:50% align:center
but maybe that kind of power is
too much for someone like me.

00:22:48.952 --> 00:22:49.953 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
Thirty years?

00:22:50.036 --> 00:22:52.080 position:50% align:center
You became a Spirit
that long ago?

00:22:52.163 --> 00:22:53.581 position:50% align:center
I had no idea.

00:22:53.665 --> 00:22:57.168 position:50% align:center
Well, to be precise,
it's more like 27 or 28.

00:22:57.252 --> 00:22:59.254 position:50% align:center
I look good for my age,
though, right?

00:22:59.337 --> 00:23:01.464 position:50% align:center
To be fair, your Spirit
power probably halted,

00:23:01.548 --> 00:23:03.717 position:50% align:center
or at least slowed
the aging process.

00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:07.595 position:50% align:center
But now you'll age like a normal
person, so better up that SPF!

00:23:07.679 --> 00:23:09.764 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Great. Love that for me.

00:23:09.848 --> 00:23:12.767 position:50% align:center
Speaking of timelines, when did
all you guys become Spirits?

00:23:12.851 --> 00:23:15.061 position:50% align:center
It's been about
five years for me.

00:23:15.145 --> 00:23:17.439 position:50% align:center
I did a year or so ago,
give or take.

00:23:17.522 --> 00:23:19.065 position:50% align:center
Not until recently.

00:23:19.149 --> 00:23:22.569 position:50% align:center
Always been one. The rest
of us are Pure Spirits.

00:23:22.652 --> 00:23:24.571 position:50% align:center
Wait, what do you mean?

00:23:24.654 --> 00:23:26.990 position:50% align:center
I thought all Spirits
were once human,

00:23:27.073 --> 00:23:29.325 position:50% align:center
at least in the
beginning of their lives.

00:23:36.082 --> 00:23:39.711 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] See the sky!
See the stars! See Mukuro!

00:23:39.794 --> 00:23:42.630 position:50% align:center
Behold, a new Spirit,
floating in the cosmos!

00:23:42.714 --> 00:23:44.883 position:50% align:center
Next time: "Space Spirit".

00:23:44.966 --> 00:23:47.385 position:50% align:center
When Earth is in trouble,
Shido will rise!

00:23:47.469 --> 00:23:49.429 position:50% align:center
Shido will fight!